<div id="main_content">
	<h2>UCF Students Use Wii and Yoga to Help Alzheimer's Patients</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By Zenaida Gonzalez Kotala
		
		<span class="date">Nov. 17, 2008</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: 345px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/1000/NE1612/en_US/backbowlingfull.jpg" height="226" width="345"  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: Ed Heiland</p>
			
			<p>Graduate students provide one-on-one therapy and then play games such as bowling with their clients through the Brain Fitness program.</p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=00240041e030fdf011daaca4445007fe4">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
					
						
						
							
